9. Important interview point: avoid retrying unsafe mutations
For GET requests, retrying is usually safe.
But for POST , PATCH , DELETE , retry carefully.
Example problem:
User clicks Pay
POST /payment succeeds on server
Network fails before frontend receives response
Frontend retries
Payment happens twice
So for critical mutations, use:
Idempotency-Key
Example:
createPayment: builder.mutation({
 query: (body) => ({
 url: "/payment",
 method: "POST",
 body,
 headers: {
 "Idempotency-Key": crypto.randomUUID(),
 },
 }),
});
Backend should store that key and ensure the same request is not processed twice.
