<h2 id="0-how-to-use-these-notes">0. How to use these notes</h2>
<p>For a lead-style interview, do not answer like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I used Lambda, S3, SQS and Glue. Lambda is serverless. S3 stores files.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Answer like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I usually explain a cloud workflow in terms of trigger, compute, state, storage, queueing, retry, 
idempotency, observability, security boundary, scaling limit, cost lever, and failure handling. For example, in 
an S3-to-Lambda-to-SQS pipeline, I would isolate raw and processed prefixes to avoid recursive triggers, use 
SQS for buffering and retry control, make the Lambda idempotent using object key/version/job id, send poison 
messages to a DLQ, and monitor iterator age/backlog, Lambda errors, duration, throttles, and DLQ count.&quot;
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is the difference between <strong>developer-level</strong> and <strong>lead-level</strong> answers.</p>
