<h2 id="7-decorators">7. Decorators</h2>
<p>A decorator wraps a function to add behavior without changing the function body.</p>
<h3 id="logging-decorator">Logging decorator</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">import functools
import time
def log_time(func):
 @functools.wraps(func)
 def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
 start = time.perf_counter()
 try:
 return func(*args, **kwargs)
 finally:
 print(f&quot;{func.__name__} took {time.perf_counter() - start:.3f}s&quot;)
 return wrapper
@log_time
def process_file():
 time.sleep(0.5)
process_file()
</code></pre>
