<h2 id="9-python-error-handling">9. Python error handling</h2>
<h3 id="good-exception-handling">Good exception handling</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">try:
 process_invoice(invoice_id)
except FileNotFoundError:
 logger.exception(&quot;Input file missing&quot;, extra={&quot;invoice_id&quot;: invoice_id})
 raise
except TimeoutError:
 logger.warning(&quot;Temporary timeout&quot;, extra={&quot;invoice_id&quot;: invoice_id})
 schedule_retry(invoice_id)
except Exception:
 logger.exception(&quot;Unexpected processing error&quot;, extra={&quot;invoice_id&quot;: invoice_id})
 raise
</code></pre>

## Page 26

<h3 id="bad-exception-handling">Bad exception handling</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">try:
 process()
except Exception:
 pass # hides production issues
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I catch exceptions at boundaries: API boundary, worker boundary, external service boundary. I log 
structured context, preserve stack traces, and decide whether to retry, fail fast, or move the job to 
DLQ.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
