<h2 id="19-lambda-s3-trigger">19. Lambda + S3 trigger</h2>
<pre><code class="language-text">User uploads file to S3 raw/
S3 ObjectCreated event invokes Lambda
Lambda validates object
Lambda sends message to SQS or starts Step Function
</code></pre>
<h3 id="common-s3-trigger-bug-recursive-loop">Common S3 trigger bug: recursive loop</h3>
<p>Bad:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">Trigger prefix: invoices/
Lambda reads invoices/a.pdf
Lambda writes invoices/a-output.json
Output write triggers same Lambda again
</code></pre>
<p>Better:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">raw/ triggers Lambda
processed/ output only, no trigger
failed/ failed files
</code></pre>
<h3 id="s3-event-handler">S3 event handler</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">from urllib.parse import unquote_plus
def lambda_handler(event, context):
 for record in event[&quot;Records&quot;]:
 bucket = record[&quot;s3&quot;][&quot;bucket&quot;][&quot;name&quot;]
 key = unquote_plus(record[&quot;s3&quot;][&quot;object&quot;][&quot;key&quot;])
 print(bucket, key)
</code></pre>
<p>Important:</p>
<ul>
<li>S3 object keys may contain spaces and URL-encoded characters.</li>
<li>Use prefix/suffix filters.</li>
<li>Make processing idempotent.</li>
<li>Do not assume one event equals exactly one business file forever.</li>
</ul>
