<h2 id="40-scenario-2-lambda-overwhelms-rds">40. Scenario 2: Lambda overwhelms RDS</h2>
<h3 id="problem">Problem</h3>
<pre><code class="language-text">Traffic spike -&gt; Lambda concurrency jumps -&gt; each invocation opens DB 
connection -&gt; RDS max connections exhausted
</code></pre>
<h3 id="fix-options">Fix options</h3>
<ol>
<li>RDS Proxy.</li>
<li>Lambda reserved concurrency.</li>
<li>Queue writes through SQS.</li>
<li>Use connection reuse.</li>
<li>Use batch writes where possible.</li>
<li>Scale DB or move high-cardinality state to DynamoDB.</li>
</ol>
<p>Interview answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I would first stabilize by limiting Lambda concurrency or temporarily disabling the trigger. Then I 
would inspect DB connections, Lambda duration, error rate, and SQS backlog. Permanent fix may include RDS 
Proxy, reserved concurrency, queue buffering, and query/index optimization.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>

