<h2 id="46-scenario-8-cost-suddenly-increases">46. Scenario 8: Cost suddenly increases</h2>
<p>Investigate:</p>
<ul>
<li>Lambda recursive loop.</li>
<li>S3 multipart uploads not completed.</li>
<li>NAT Gateway data processing charges.</li>
<li>CloudWatch logs too verbose.</li>
<li>Glue jobs over-provisioned or stuck.</li>
<li>SQS backlog with retries.</li>
<li>Data transfer across AZ/Region.</li>
<li>Unused EBS/EIP/RDS snapshots.</li>
</ul>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Cost incidents are production incidents. I check cost explorer, service-level usage metrics, recent 
deployments, recursive event patterns, and unbounded retries. Then I add guardrails such as budgets, alarms, 
