<h2 id="12-lambda-concurrency-and-scaling">12. Lambda concurrency and scaling</h2>
<p>Concurrency means number of in-flight Lambda invocations at the same time. A practical formula is:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">concurrency = requests per second * average duration in seconds
</code></pre>
<p>Example:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">100 requests/sec * 0.5 sec = 50 concurrent executions
100 requests/sec * 5 sec = 500 concurrent executions
</code></pre>
