<h2 id="25-dlq-and-poison-messages">25. DLQ and poison messages</h2>
<p>A poison message is a message that repeatedly fails due to invalid data or a non-transient bug.</p>
<h3 id="dlq-flow">DLQ flow</h3>
<pre><code class="language-text">SQS main queue
 -&gt; message fails
 -&gt; retried until maxReceiveCount
 -&gt; moved to DLQ
</code></pre>
<h3 id="dlq-is-not-a-trash-bin">DLQ is not a trash bin</h3>

## Page 120

<p>You need:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- CloudWatch alarm on DLQ depth &gt; 0
- dashboard for failed message types
- replay script/tool
- ability to patch bad data or code before replay
- retention policy
</code></pre>
<h3 id="dlq-replay-checklist">DLQ replay checklist</h3>
<pre><code class="language-text">1. Identify failure reason.
2. Fix code/config/data.
3. Confirm idempotency.
4. Replay small batch first.
5. Monitor errors and downstream load.
6. Replay remaining messages gradually.
</code></pre>
