</tr>
<tr>
 <td>SQS</td>
 <td>Durable queue/buffer</td>
 <td>One consumer group processes jobs</td>
</tr>
<tr>
 <td>EventBridge</td>
 <td>Event bus/routing</td>
 <td>Domain events, SaaS integrations, rules</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Example:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">OrderCreated event
 -&gt; EventBridge bus
 -&gt; billing service
 -&gt; notification service
 -&gt; analytics service
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;If I need durable job processing, I use SQS. If I need fanout, I use SNS or EventBridge. If I need 
domain event routing with rules and multiple targets, EventBridge is usually cleaner.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
