<h2 id="32-spark-basics-you-need-for-glue">32. Spark basics you need for Glue</h2>
<h3 id="driver-vs-executor">Driver vs executor</h3>
<pre><code class="language-text">Driver:
 - coordinates job
 - builds execution plan
 - tracks tasks
Executors:
 - run tasks on partitions
 - process data in parallel
</code></pre>
<h3 id="partitioning">Partitioning</h3>
<p>Spark processes data in partitions. Bad partitioning causes poor performance.</p>
<p>Problems:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">Too few partitions -&gt; not enough parallelism
Too many partitions -&gt; scheduling overhead
Skewed partitions -&gt; one executor does most work
Small files -&gt; too many tasks and S3 overhead
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;In Glue/Spark performance issues, I check input file sizes, number of partitions, shuffle stages,

## Page 124

skew, worker type, executor memory, and whether filters are pushed down before wide transformations.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
