<h2 id="53-playbook-glue-oom">53. Playbook: Glue OOM</h2>
<p>Symptoms:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- executor lost
- Java heap space
- container killed
- driver memory error
</code></pre>
<p>Causes:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- collect() or toPandas()
- skewed join/groupBy
- huge shuffle
- too few workers
- wrong worker type
- too many small files
- uncompressed data
</code></pre>
<p>Fixes:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- filter/select early
- avoid collect
- repartition strategically
- broadcast small table
- use Parquet
- increase worker type/count
- compact files
- handle skewed keys
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h2 id="54-playbook-rds-connection-exhaustion">54. Playbook: RDS connection exhaustion</h2>
<p>Symptoms:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- too many clients already
- connection timeout
- high DB connections metric
- API failures during spike
</code></pre>
<p>Causes:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- Lambda opened too many connections
- no pooling/proxy
- leaked connections
- long transactions
</code></pre>
<p>Fix:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- RDS Proxy
- reserved concurrency
- close connections safely
- reuse pool in containers
- reduce transaction time
- async queue writes
</code></pre>
