<h2 id="66-boto3-paginator-pattern">66. boto3 paginator pattern</h2>
<p>Many AWS APIs return paginated responses. Do not assume one call returns all data.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">import boto3
s3 = boto3.client(&quot;s3&quot;)
def list_all_keys(bucket, prefix):
 paginator = s3.get_paginator(&quot;list_objects_v2&quot;)
 for page in paginator.paginate(Bucket=bucket, Prefix=prefix):
 for obj in page.get(&quot;Contents&quot;, []):
 yield obj[&quot;Key&quot;]
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;For AWS list APIs, I use paginators. Missing pagination is a common production bug that only appears 
when data grows.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
