 filename = Path(key).name
 local_path = f&quot;/tmp/{filename}&quot;
 s3.download_file(bucket, key, local_path)
 return local_path
</code></pre>
<p>Cautions:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- /tmp has limited storage depending on configuration.
- Clean up large files.
- Do not trust filename blindly for security-sensitive paths.
- Avoid processing files larger than Lambda can handle.
</code></pre>
