<p>If Lambda keeps scaling too much and you want to prevent too many parallel executions, think 
<strong>reserved concurrency</strong>. If you want to reduce cold starts by keeping execution environments 
warm, think <strong>provisioned concurrency</strong>. They solve different problems.</p>
