<h2 id="104-presigned-s3-upload-visual-route-map">104. Presigned S3 upload - visual route map</h2>
<p>For large uploads, do not upload the file through API Gateway/Lambda unless the file is small and the 
latency is acceptable. Generate a presigned URL, upload directly to S3, and trigger async processing.</p>
<div class="flow-visual"><div class="flow-node">React client</div><div class="flow-arrow">1. request upload 
URL</div><div class="flow-node">API Lambda</div><div class="flow-arrow">2. presigned URL</div><div class="flow-
node">React client</div><div class="flow-arrow">3. PUT file</div><div class="flow-node">S3 raw bucket</div><div 
class="flow-arrow">4. event</div><div class="flow-node">SQS/Lambda worker</div></div>
<pre><code class="language-python">import boto3
s3 = boto3.client("s3")
def create_upload_url(bucket: str, key: str, content_type: str):
 return s3.generate_presigned_url(
 ClientMethod="put_object",
 Params={
 "Bucket": bucket,
 "Key": key,
 "ContentType": content_type,
 },
 ExpiresIn=900,
 )</code></pre>
<p><strong>Interview answer:</strong> "For large file uploads, I avoid passing the binary through Lambda. I use 
presigned S3 upload, then process asynchronously through S3 event/SQS/Lambda/Step Functions."</p>
<h2 id="105-console-debugging-playbook-where-to-click-first">105. Console debugging playbook - where to click 
first</h2>
<table><thead><tr><th>Problem</th><th>Console path</th><th>First things to check</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Lambda throttling</td><td>Lambda -> Monitor -> Metrics; Configuration -> Concurrency</td><td>Reserved 
concurrency, account concurrency, SQS max concurrency, downstream limits</td></tr>
<tr><td>SQS backlog growing</td><td>SQS -> Monitoring; Lambda -> Triggers/Monitor</td><td>Oldest message age, 
Lambda errors/throttles, batch size, visibility timeout</td></tr>
<tr><td>AccessDenied</td><td>CloudWatch logs; IAM role; CloudTrail</td><td>Failing action, resource ARN, 
identity policy, resource policy, KMS policy</td></tr>
<tr><td>S3 trigger loop</td><td>S3 -> Properties -> Event notifications; Lambda -> Monitor</td>
<td>Prefix/suffix, output prefix, recent deployment, recursive writes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Glue OOM</td><td>Glue -> Job runs -> Logs; CloudWatch</td><td>Driver/executor logs, skew, shuffle, 
worker type/count, input files</td></tr>
<tr><td>API Gateway 502</td><td>API Gateway -> Logs; Lambda -> Logs</td><td>Proxy response format, unhandled 
exception, timeout, permissions</td></tr>
<tr><td>RDS connection exhaustion</td><td>RDS -> Monitoring; Lambda -> Concurrency</td><td>Connection count, 
Lambda concurrency, pooling, RDS Proxy, leaked sessions</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
