<h2 id="107-interview-demo-script-for-visual-aws-questions">107. Interview demo script for visual AWS 
questions</h2>
<p>If they ask, "How would you configure this in AWS?", answer in this structure:</p>
<blockquote><p>"First I would choose the event model. If it is file upload, I prefer S3 direct upload with a 
presigned URL. Then I create an S3 event notification filtered by prefix/suffix and send it to SQS instead of 
directly to Lambda if I need buffering. Then the Lambda SQS trigger has batch size, partial batch failure, and 
maximum concurrency configured. The Lambda itself has a timeout, memory, execution role, environment variables, 
and reserved concurrency if needed. For failure handling, the queue has a DLQ and the Lambda is idempotent. For 
debugging, I check CloudWatch logs, Lambda metrics, SQS oldest message age, DLQ count, and CloudTrail for 
permission issues."</p></blockquote>
<p>This sounds like someone who understands both the console and the production behavior behind the console.
</p>
