<h2 id="23-s3-security">23. S3 security</h2>
<p>Checklist:</p>
<ul>
<li>Block public access unless explicitly needed.</li>
<li>Use bucket policies carefully.</li>
<li>Use IAM roles, not hardcoded keys.</li>
<li>Use KMS encryption where required.</li>
<li>Use pre-signed URLs for controlled temporary access.</li>
<li>Enable versioning for critical data.</li>
<li>Use lifecycle rules to control cost.</li>
<li>Log access when needed.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="pre-signed-uploaddownload">Pre-signed upload/download</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">url = s3.generate_presigned_url(
 ClientMethod=&quot;get_object&quot;,
 Params={&quot;Bucket&quot;: &quot;my-bucket&quot;, &quot;Key&quot;: &quot;raw/invoice.pdf&quot;},
 ExpiresIn=900,
)
</code></pre>
<p>Use case:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">Frontend asks API for upload URL
API validates user and returns pre-signed PUT URL
Frontend uploads directly to S3
S3 event starts processing
</code></pre>
<p>This avoids sending large files through your API server.</p>
