)
</code></pre>
<h3 id="lambda-rds-issue">Lambda + RDS issue</h3>
<p>Lambda can scale faster than RDS connection capacity.</p>
<p>Bad:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">1000 Lambda invocations
 -&gt; each opens DB connection
 -&gt; DB max connections exhausted
</code></pre>
<p>Fixes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use RDS Proxy.</li>
<li>Set Lambda reserved concurrency.</li>
<li>Reuse connections carefully in warm containers.</li>
<li>Use connection pooling in container apps.</li>
<li>Move heavy async writes to SQS worker.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="rds-high-availability">RDS high availability</h3>
<p>Multi-AZ helps availability by failing over to standby when primary fails. Application must handle 
connection drops and retries.</p>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Multi-AZ does not mean zero downtime. I expect brief failover and design the application with retry, 
connection refresh, and idempotency.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
