<h2 id="2-python-memory-references-and-leaks">2. Python memory, references, and leaks</h2>
<p>Python variables are references to objects. This matters in AWS workers because a Lambda execution 
environment can be reused. Global mutable state can survive across invocations.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">cache = {}

