<h2 id="5-idempotency-in-python-workers">5. Idempotency in Python workers</h2>
<p>Idempotency means processing the same event multiple times does not create wrong duplicate side effects.</p>
<h3 id="why-idempotency-is-mandatory-in-aws">Why idempotency is mandatory in AWS</h3>
<p>Many AWS event sources are at-least-once. SQS, SNS, EventBridge, Lambda async retries, and network failures 
can cause duplicate processing.</p>
<h3 id="idempotent-sqs-processing-pattern">Idempotent SQS processing pattern</h3>
<pre><code class="language-python">import hashlib
from datetime import datetime
def make_idempotency_key(message: dict) -&gt; str:
 raw = f&quot;{message['job_id']}:{message['s3_bucket']}:{message['s3_key']}:{message.get('version_id', 
'')}&quot;
 return hashlib.sha256(raw.encode()).hexdigest()
def process_message(message, repository):
 key = make_idempotency_key(message)
 if repository.already_processed(key):
 return {&quot;status&quot;: &quot;skipped_duplicate&quot;, &quot;idempotency_key&quot;: key}
 repository.mark_processing(key, started_at=datetime.utcnow())
 try:
 result = run_business_logic(message)
 repository.mark_success(key, result=result)
 return result
 except Exception as exc:
 repository.mark_failed(key, error=str(exc))
 raise
</code></pre>
<p>Database table idea:</p>
<pre><code class="language-sql">CREATE TABLE processed_events (
 idempotency_key TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
 status TEXT NOT NULL,
 started_at TIMESTAMP,
 completed_at TIMESTAMP,
 error_message TEXT
);
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I design idempotency before retries. Otherwise retries can create duplicate files, duplicate DB rows, 
duplicate emails, duplicate payments, or inconsistent statuses.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
