<h1 id="part-v2-f---step-functions-deep-dive">PART V2-F - Step Functions Deep Dive</h1>
<h2 id="28-why-step-functions">28. Why Step Functions</h2>
<p>Step Functions orchestrates workflows. It is useful when multiple steps need state, retries, branching, 
waiting, or visibility.</p>
<p>Use Step Functions when:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- workflow has multiple dependent steps
- human-readable execution history is useful
- each step may need retry/catch
- long-running orchestration is needed
- parallel/map processing is needed
</code></pre>
<p>Do not use Step Functions for everything:</p>
<pre><code class="language-text">- very simple single-step async jobs may only need SQS + Lambda
- ultra-high-frequency tiny events may be cost-sensitive
</code></pre>
<h3 id="standard-vs-express">Standard vs Express</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
 <th>Type</th>
 <th>Best for</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
 <td>Standard</td>
 <td>Long-running, auditable workflows, exactly-once workflow execution semantics</td>
</tr>
<tr>

## Page 287

<td>Express</td>
 <td>High-volume short-duration workflows, lower cost for high throughput</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2 id="29-retry-and-catch">29. Retry and Catch</h2>
<p>Step Functions can retry failed states and then catch errors if retries are exhausted.</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
 &quot;StartAt&quot;: &quot;ProcessFile&quot;,
 &quot;States&quot;: {
 &quot;ProcessFile&quot;: {
 &quot;Type&quot;: &quot;Task&quot;,
 &quot;Resource&quot;: &quot;arn:aws:lambda:ap-south-1:123:function:process-file&quot;,
 &quot;Retry&quot;: [
 {
 &quot;ErrorEquals&quot;: [&quot;Lambda.ServiceException&quot;, 
&quot;Lambda.TooManyRequestsException&quot;],
 &quot;IntervalSeconds&quot;: 2,
 &quot;MaxAttempts&quot;: 3,
 &quot;BackoffRate&quot;: 2.0
 }
 ],
 &quot;Catch&quot;: [
 {
 &quot;ErrorEquals&quot;: [&quot;States.ALL&quot;],
 &quot;Next&quot;: &quot;MarkFailed&quot;
 }
 ],
 &quot;Next&quot;: &quot;MarkSuccess&quot;
 },
 &quot;MarkFailed&quot;: {&quot;Type&quot;: &quot;Pass&quot;, &quot;End&quot;: true},
 &quot;MarkSuccess&quot;: {&quot;Type&quot;: &quot;Pass&quot;, &quot;End&quot;: true}
 }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Lead answer:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I use Step Functions when I need workflow visibility and step-level retry/catch. I keep each Lambda 
step idempotent because retries can execute a step again.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2 id="30-distributed-map-use-case">30. Distributed Map use case</h2>
