<h2 id="106-cli-equivalents-for-console-settings">106. CLI equivalents for console settings</h2>
<p>In interview, knowing the console is good. Knowing the CLI/IaC equivalent makes you sound more senior 
because real production systems should be repeatable.</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"># Lambda metrics-related config
aws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name invoice-worker
# Lambda reserved concurrency
aws lambda put-function-concurrency \
 --function-name invoice-worker \
 --reserved-concurrent-executions 25
# List Lambda event source mappings
aws lambda list-event-source-mappings \
 --function-name invoice-worker
# Update SQS trigger batch size / partial batch response
aws lambda update-event-source-mapping \
 --uuid EVENT_SOURCE_MAPPING_UUID \
 --batch-size 10 \
 --function-response-types ReportBatchItemFailures \
 --scaling-config MaximumConcurrency=20
# Read SQS queue attributes
aws sqs get-queue-attributes \
 --queue-url QUEUE_URL \
 --attribute-names All
# Get Glue job details
aws glue get-job --job-name invoice-etl
# Start Glue job with params
aws glue start-job-run \
 --job-name invoice-etl \
 --arguments '{"--source_path":"s3://raw/invoices/","--target_path":"s3://curated/invoices/"}'</code></pre>
<h2 id="107-interview-demo-script-for-visual-aws-questions">107. Interview demo script for visual AWS 
questions</h2>
<p>If they ask, "How would you configure this in AWS?", answer in this structure:</p>
<blockquote><p>"First I would choose the event model. If it is file upload, I prefer S3 direct upload with a 
presigned URL. Then I create an S3 event notification filtered by prefix/suffix and send it to SQS instead of 
directly to Lambda if I need buffering. Then the Lambda SQS trigger has batch size, partial batch failure, and 
maximum concurrency configured. The Lambda itself has a timeout, memory, execution role, environment variables, 
and reserved concurrency if needed. For failure handling, the queue has a DLQ and the Lambda is idempotent. For 
debugging, I check CloudWatch logs, Lambda metrics, SQS oldest message age, DLQ count, and CloudTrail for 
permission issues."</p></blockquote>
<p>This sounds like someone who understands both the console and the production behavior behind the console.
</p>
